			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3759263">
									

<p>I had an idea, but I wanted to bring it up here rather than attempt to set a precedent about this SCP: what does 3922 do with works of historical fiction?</p>
<p>My example is the musical 1776, which is about the (not-yet) US Congress in the days leading up to declaring independence against Britain. Which would be more likely:</p>
<p>1. Cobernic troops storm the hall during the opening number and detain the members of all legislatures of colonies where slavery was legal at the time, or,</p>
<p>2. As the film does not deviate meaningfully from known US history, there is no interference, save for the scene in which Edward Rutledge criticizes Thomas Jefferson for advocating abolition while still owning slaves. When a tense Jefferson responds with a vow to free his slaves, a Cobernic trooper is shown just out of focus, nodding sternly.</p>

